of cleft lip?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Failure of fusion of the two lateral palatine shelves","Failure of migration of neural crest cells","Failure of fusion of the maxillary and medial nasal processes","Failure of formation of the primary palate","Failure of the frontonasal prominence to develop"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ECleft lip results from \u003Cstrong\u003Efailure of fusion of the maxillary and medial nasal processes\u003C/strong\u003E during weeks 4-7 of embryonic development. This fusion is essential for normal formation of the upper lip and primary palate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFailure of fusion of the two lateral palatine shelves\u003C/strong\u003E describes one mechanism of cleft palate formation, which is embryologically distinct from cleft lip\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFailure of migration of neural crest cells\u003C/strong\u003E would result in more widespread facial development problems\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFailure of formation of the primary palate\u003C/strong\u003E would affect the anterior portion of the palate but not directly cause cleft lip\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFailure of the frontonasal prominence to develop\u003C/strong\u003E would result in more severe midface defects\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile cleft lip and cleft palate can occur together (in about 50% of cases), they have distinct embryological origins and can occur independently.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Cleft lip occurs due to failed fusion of maxillary and medial nasal processes during weeks 4-7 of embryonic development","Cleft lip is distinct from cleft palate, which involves failed fusion of palatine shelves","Cleft lip affects approximately 1 in 1000 live births in Australia"],"references":["Vyas T, Gupta P, Kumar S, Gupta R, Gupta T, Singh HP. Cleft of lip and palate: A review. J Family Med Prim Care. 2020 Jun 30;9(6):2621-2625. doi: 10.4103/jfmpc.jfmpc_472_20. PMID: 32984097; PMCID: PMC7491837.","Pang J, Broyles J, Redett R. Cleft lip and palate. Eplasty. 2013;13:ic25. Epub 2013 Jan 30. PMID: 23409216; PMCID: PMC3567612.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58941"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16013"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58941","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58941"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-23T21:41:35+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-23T21:43:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8704"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73472"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emed